premise: Cashew apple offers several advantages over other sources of feedstocks for biofuel: (i) cashew apple juice (CAJ) extracted from the apple contains abundant reducing sugars (50-200 g/L); (ii) CAJ is rich in organic acid, minerals and amino acids necessary for yeast growth; (iii) it is inexpensive source of sugars; (iv) pretreatment method is simple and hydrolysis is not required; (v) it avoids food security issues, and readily available in large quantities as cashew apples are neglected in their cultivation areas after harvesting of the nut.
